    "description": {
      "value": "<p>@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.WklldBUUO3oesibI]{UM5 Ch.6: Granades &amp; Explosives} @Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-weaponproperties.a6bTH9RIOA1gwoza]{Grenade}&nbsp; @Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-weaponproperties.tyqnHVNxWuUF1jDk]{EXP (Explosives)} @Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-weaponproperties.6mwuvYMwCZg5yRvC]{(EXP) H.E.A.T.} @Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-weaponproperties.iK2nOll8s5dIVgVp]{AP}&nbsp;@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.oaLjWnlYGoulu7oy]{Tech Level 1}</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Or high-explosive anti-tank, HEAT is able to generate extreme temperature in a focused burst, compromising virtually any defense. When focused into a shaped charge, a HEAT weapon is the greatest threat to armored opponents.<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"></span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">HEAT explosives have the AP property, and also count as fire and radiant against targets resistant to those types.</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<table class=\"NormalTable\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">HEAT </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">2d6 </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Physical </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">5 ft. </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Â½ lb. </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">45 </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">1 </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">No </span></td>\n<td width=\"200\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Detonator</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><span style=\"font-size: 1.5em;\">Physical</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Grenades and explosives with the physical damage type deal bludgeoning damage unless otherwise stated. Medium or smaller targets that don't save against the Dexterity saving throw are knocked prone by the explosion.</span></p>",
